HTTP is unsecured connection, while HTTPS is secured connection in Encrypted 
HTTP sends data over port 80 while HTTPS uses port 443. 
HTTP operates at application layer, while HTTPS operates at transport layer.(TLS --> Transport Layer Security) 
No SSL certificates are required for HTTP, with HTTPS it is required that you have an SSL( Secure Sockets Layer) certificate and it is signed by a CA.
SSL--> standard security technology that establishes an encrypted connection between a web server and a browser.
